---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const title = "Privacy Policy";
const description = "Privacy policy and data protection guidelines for HomeProjectHub.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-6 py-4">
    <nav class="flex items-center gap-1.5 text-xs text-[var(--fg-muted)] mb-6" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-[var(--fg)] transition-colors">Home</a>
      <svg class="w-3 h-3" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="m9 18 6-6-6-6"/></svg>
      <span class="text-[var(--fg-secondary)] font-medium">Privacy Policy</span>
    </nav>

    <header class="pb-6 mb-2 border-b border-[var(--border)]">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-balance mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xs text-[var(--fg-muted)] font-mono">
        Last Updated: June 30, 2026
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 text-sm text-[var(--fg-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        At HomeProjectHub, accessible from https://homeprojecthub.com, one of our main priorities is the privacy of our visitors. This Privacy Policy document contains types of information that is collected and recorded by HomeProjectHub and how we use it.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
        Consent
      </h2>
      <p>
        By using our website, you hereby consent to our Privacy Policy and agree to its terms.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
        Information We Collect
      </h2>
      <p>
        The personal information that you are asked to provide, and the reasons why you are asked to provide it, will be made clear to you at the point we ask you to provide your personal information.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you contact us directly, we may receive additional information about you such as your name, email address, phone number, the contents of the message and/or attachments you may send us, and any other information you may choose to provide.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
        How We Use Your Information
      </h2>
      <p>We use the information we collect in various ways, including to:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 flex flex-col gap-2 text-sm text-[var(--fg-secondary)]">
        <li>Provide, operate, and maintain our website.</li>
        <li>Improve, personalize, and expand our website.</li>
        <li>Understand and analyze how you use our website.</li>
        <li>Develop new products, services, features, and functionality.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
        Analytics
      </h2>
      <p>
        HomeProjectHub does not load Google Analytics unless a valid analytics ID is configured for the production site. If analytics is enabled, it may collect standard usage data such as page views, device information, and approximate geography to help improve the website.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
        Local Browser Storage (LocalStorage)
      </h2>
      <p>
        To provide room workspace features, HomeProjectHub stores dimensions locally in your browser's <code>localStorage</code>. This data never leaves your device and is not transmitted to our servers. You can clear this data at any time by clearing your browser cache or deleting individual items in the Saved Rooms dashboard.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
        Advertising Partners (Google AdSense)
      </h2>
      <p>
        Third-party ad servers or ad networks use technologies like cookies, JavaScript, or Web Beacons that are used in their respective advertisements and links that appear on HomeProjectHub, which are sent directly to users' browsers. They automatically receive your IP address when this occurs. These technologies are used to measure the effectiveness of their advertising campaigns and/or to personalize the advertising content that you see on websites that you visit.
      </p>
      <p>
        Note that HomeProjectHub has no access to or control over these cookies that are used by third-party advertisers.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-3 text-[var(--fg)]">
        Affiliate Links
      </h2>
      <p>
        Some outbound shopping links may be affiliate links. If you click one of those links and make a purchase, HomeProjectHub may earn a commission at no additional cost to you. Affiliate links do not change the estimates shown by our calculators.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
